{"article_id":"MiYFattojFsLfJgW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Interest rates on student loans are set to double on Monday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"after lawmakers failed to find a bipartisan solution","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to keep the federally subsidized borrowing costs down .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The Senate adjourned Thursday night for the July 4 recess","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"without approving a student loan rate package .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"With the current , 3.4 percent interest rate on Stafford loans","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"-- the most popular funding for college students -","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"set to expire on July 1 ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"a host of 11th-hour fixes all failed to generate support from both sides of the aisle .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Without new legislation","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"-- either to extend the cap ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"set a new one","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"or find another way","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"to peg the loans -","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"the cap rises to 6.8 percent .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Congress could always forge a solution in the following days ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"even lowering rates retroactively .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The higher rates would add about $ 3,000 to the total interest on a $ 23,000 student loan","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"repaid over 10 years .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"\" At one level it ' s modest ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"if you have an entry-level position","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"or can ' t find work ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"it starts to add up , \"","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Terry Hartle , senior vice president of the American Council of Education , told FoxNews.com .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Democrats have sought to keep interest on Stafford loans low ,","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"saying","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"poor and middle class students need the help","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"to get college educations .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"seeking to cut , or at least control spending ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"have proposed linking student loans to the financial markets","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"instead of letting Congress set federal lending rates .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"President Obama included a variation of that market-based approach in the budget","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"he sent to Congress earlier this year ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"leaving his fellow Democrats trying to block his efforts .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"`` Why Senate Democrats continue to attack the president 's plan is a mystery to me ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"but I hope","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"he 's able to persuade them to join our bipartisan effort","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"to assist students , ''","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"said Don Stewart , a spokesman for Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid said recently","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"that the plan","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"to tie rates to the 10-year treasury note yield","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"could never pass","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"and that he couldn ' t back something","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that doesn ' t include stronger protections for students and parents .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"\" There is no deal on student loans","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"that can pass the Senate","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"because Republicans continue to insist","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"that we reduce the deficit on the backs of students and middle-class families ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"instead of closing tax loopholes for the wealthiest Americans and big corporations , \"","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Adam Jentleson , a spokesman for Reid , told .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"\" Senate Democrats continue to work in good faith","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"to reach a compromise","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"but Republicans refuse to give on this critical point . \"","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"Democrats said","depth":3},{"id":57,"text":"the Senate would vote on July 10 on a one-year extension of the current interest rates .","depth":3},{"id":58,"text":"But","depth":4},{"id":59,"text":"once rates rise ,","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"some experts fear","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"generating votes","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"to rein them back in","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"could prove difficult .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"\" The sense of urgency could be lost , \"","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Hartle said ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"\" And that means interest rates will [ stay ] higher . \"","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"Some undergraduates currently pay 3.4 percent","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"or some pay 6.8 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"depending on their loan structures","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and many students borrow at both rates .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Graduate students and parents borrow from the government at 7.9 percent interest under the current system .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"Few students are expected to sign loan documents in July","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"and instead were looking to finalize the aid packages closer to returning to campus in the fall .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"\" Federal loans are still one of the best options , \"","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Hartle said .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"\" But we could see students","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"that are a little pinched by these rates . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":155,"left":133,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":102,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":82,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":82,"left":80,"right":81,"relation":"elaboratio